collection.prompt: Divisions are used to represent our leagues. They are organized into a hierarchical tree data structure and stored as nested sets. Each set is grouped by its 'root_id' which is the 'division_id' of the root node of that league tree.

data.name: page_size
data.prompt: The number of items to return for each page. Sending this parameter with the query will enable paging for the returned collection.

data.name: page_number
data.prompt: The number of the page to be returned. This requires that paging be turned on by also providing the page_size parameter.

queries.prompt: Returns all the nested set ancestors of the given division.
Returns all the nested set descendants of the given division.
Returns all the nested set children of the given division.
Beta: (This endpoint subject to change) Returns all the nested set leaves of the given division. A leaf is a division that has no child divisions.
Finds all active trial divisions for a given user. Excludes archived and disabled divisions.
Finds all active root divisions for a given owner or commissioner. Excludes archived and disabled divisions.
Beta: (This endpoint subject to change) Return the ancestors, the division and the children divisions.

data.name: root_id
data.prompt: Beta: This data's name and value are subject to change.

data.name: left_boundary
data.prompt: Beta: (This attribute is subject to change or sudden removal) Used in constructing the tree of divisions, this is the left boundary of this division in the nested set of divisions under the root_id

data.prompt: Beta: (This attribute is subject to change or sudden removal) Used in constructing the tree of divisions, this is the right boundary of this division in the nested set of divisions under the root_id
